# Thermal Camera Monitor
Raspberry Pi based thermal monitoring system with a web-based dashboard.

## Installation
0. Create pyton env: python3 -m venv opencv
1. Install dependencies: `pip install flask numpy<2 opencv=4.6.*`
2. Setup camera quirks:
	sudo nano /etc/modprobe.d/uvcvideo.conf
        options uvcvideo quirks=0x2
2. Set up the service: `sudo cp thermal.service /etc/systemd/system/`
at /etc/systemd/system/thermal.service 
[Unit]
Description=Thermal Camera Monitor Service
After=network.target

[Service]
# Adjust these paths to match your actual setup
User=vadim
WorkingDirectory=/home/vadim/opencv
ExecStart=/home/vadim/opencv/bin/python3 /home/vadim/opencv/flask_ui.py
Restart=always
RestartSec=10
StandardOutput=null
StandardError=inherit

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

3. Enable startup: `sudo systemctl enable thermal.service`
4. sudo systemctl start thermal.service
